00:22.153 --> 00:27.078
Alice said, and I quote, would you please tell me which way all to go from here?

00:27.098 --> 00:31.122
Famously, the Cheshire cat responded,

00:31.714 --> 00:35.197
That depends a good deal on where you want to get to.

00:35.237 --> 00:46.488
Alice responded, I don't much care where to which the cat responded, then it doesn't much matter which way you go.

00:46.508 --> 01:00.562
And Alice said, so long as I get somewhere, the response, oh, you're sure to do that if only you walk long enough.

01:01.442 --> 01:09.815
I'm reminded of that story often because I experienced so many people who really don't know where they're going.

01:10.816 --> 01:27.922
Isn't it so easy just to get in a rut and a routine of fumbling through life, getting caught up in the tyranny of the urgent, whatever the next thing is that occupies your mind, the next home improvement, the next vacation, the next

01:28.322 --> 01:32.927
family tension, the next workday, the next whatever he is.

01:34.188 --> 01:49.805
And I believe so many people live without a sense of true direction and understanding of how short this life is and how important and clear the mission is that God has given us.

01:51.166 --> 01:54.610
And so often so many just go through the motions.

01:54.850 --> 02:18.626
live through vanity fair, as John Bunyan said, being pulled by pleasures on the left hand and the right, just getting in the lazy river at the water park and just floating with the culture wherever it goes, or maybe having tunnel vision and getting fixed on one particular financial goal or hobby or material desire or whatever it is.

02:19.867 --> 02:21.650
I want to ask you, what is the aim?

02:21.690 --> 02:24.274
What is the trajectory of your life?

02:25.026 --> 02:42.794
If your life continues in the way that you are currently living it, what is the natural outcome of that lifestyle, of the way that you spend your time and your money, of the things that occupy your heart, of the things that you give yourself on a daily basis?

02:43.415 --> 02:53.170
What is the aim and the trajectory that that arrow is flying at and will hit if you continue the way that you're living?

02:54.946 --> 03:06.661
I want us to step back from the verse by verse exposition that we do, and we're fully committed to every Sunday and every Wednesday of the year for hours every week.

